Biology. The species has a very wide spectrum of ecological preferences. It inhabits wet and dry meadows, steppes, and semideserts; also, is quite common on alfalfa fields. For example, in the central part of Dzhungarsky Alatau Mtn. Range it was found in the steppes at the foothills, on dry mountain slopes and in wet meadow on the riverbank in a ravine. It was collected from Asteraceae (
Artemisia , Achillea
), Chenopodiaceae (
Camphorosma
) and Fabaceae (cultivated alfalfa and several wild species including
Trifolium
).
